
[1]frankness

   FRANK'NESS, n.

   1. Plainness of speech; candor; freedom in communication; openness;
   ingenuousness. He told me his opinions with frankness.

   2. Fairness; freedom from art or craft; as frankness of dealing.

   3. Liberality; bounteousness. [Little used.]
